 century. It includes texts by 47 authors from different religious denominations along with commentary, an afterword, and detailed name and subject indexes. The two-volume work provides insight into this original debate on media in the German-speaking world, furnishing an unprecedented level of detail and information.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 4aBilderstreit. 4aBildkritik. 4aBildtheorie. 4aZensur. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh  aCensorship.  aIconic criticism.  aIconoclastic Controversy.  aImage theory.1 aAlpinus, Marcus Tatius, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAnonymer,, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAnonymus,, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aArndt, Johann, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBerns, Jörg Jochen, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBodenstein, Andreas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBucer, Martin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBuchstab, Johannes, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBullinger, Heinrich, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aButzbach, Johannes, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCalvin, Johannes, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCastiglione, Baldassare, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChemnitz, Martin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCochlæus, Johannes, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDietenberger, Johannes, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/re